  "prompt": "How do I get over a crush on my guy best friend?",
  "response": "Getting over a crush on a close friend can be challenging, but there are several strategies you can try to help you move on:\n\n1. **Acknowledge Your Feelings**: Accept that it's normal to have feelings for a close friend. Allow yourself to feel those emotions without judgment.\n\n2. **Reflect on Your Crush**: Consider why you developed feelings for him. Is it his personality, looks, or something else? Understanding the basis of your feelings can help you recognize them as temporary.\n\n3. **Set Boundaries**: If being around him makes it harder to move on, consider creating some distance. This doesn't mean cutting him out of your life completely, but maybe reducing the time you spend together for a while.\n\n4. **Focus on Yourself**: Engage in activities that you enjoy or try new hobbies. Investing time in yourself can help shift your focus away from your crush.\n\n5. **Talk to Someone**: Sharing your feelings with a trusted friend or family member can provide support and perspective.\n\n6. **Get to Know Other People**: Opening yourself up to meeting new people may help distract you from your crush and might even lead to new romantic interests.\n\n7. **Redirect Your Thoughts**: When you find yourself thinking about him, consciously shift your focus to other thoughts or activities.\n\n8. **Practice Acceptance**: Understand that friendships can evolve, and it's okay if your feelings don't reciprocate. Accepting the situation can be a crucial step toward moving on.\n\n9. **Be Patient**: Give yourself time to heal; feelings don't change overnight. It\u2019s important to be patient with yourself as you work through your emotions.\n\nRemember, it\u2019s okay to still value your friendship. With time and effort, it is possible to move past your crush and maintain a healthy friendship.",
